I don't think falling behind is valid grounds for an incomplete

Correct, to receive an imcomplete, you must have been doing well through the vast ajority of the course, and then an extenuating circumstance prevents you from completing it (ie. concussion during week 14)
Is there any way you can incomplete the course instead?

history.content: I wouldn't be too worried. The only company that ever asked me for my transcript was Google. And I'm pretty sure they just looked at your GPA number. All the others you've heard of (Facebook, Amazon, Uber, Dropbox, PInterest, Airbnb, ... on and on) have never asked me for my transcript.

Hi, 3rd year CS Major here. I'm currently taking Stats 134 p/np because I'm taking an incredibly heavy workload and had very little time to devote for that class.I should've planned out my schedule better the beginning of this semester. Unfortunately, it looks like I'm in danger of failing this class at the moment. Given that a failed class doesn't count towards your gpa, and that my GPA is pretty good (3.59), how worried should I be about this NP in Stats 134? I  have ample outside experience, including internships after my 1st and 2nd years. Also, given the fact that internship employers typically only see your trasncript after the offer, should I mention it anytime before the offer that I failed a class? Thank you!
